<TITLE> Youth jailed for 20kgs of deer meat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Satkhira, Apr 17 (bdnews24.com)  Villagers handed over a youth with 20kgs of deer meat to the police in Satkhira Saturday. The detained, Ariful Islam, is the son of Ansar Ali of Shimulia village under Debhata upazila. Fazlur Rahman, officer in charge of Ashashuni Police Station, said that the villagers suspected Ariful when he was crossing Manik Khali by boat. The locals caught him when the youth tried to escape after they discovered the deer meat in his bag. Being informed, the police brought him to the police station with the meat. Fazlur said that it would be investigated whether the meat was of deer or not. Ariful was sent to jail through the court in the afternoon. A case was also lodged against him. bdnews
